{{title|1=operator==, operator&lt;=&gt;&lt;small&gt;(std::stacktrace_entry)&lt;/small&gt;}}
{{cpp/utility/stacktrace_entry/navbar}}
{{dcl begin}}
{{dcl|num=1|since=c++23|1=
friend constexpr bool operator==( const stacktrace_entry&amp; lhs,
                                  const stacktrace_entry&amp; rhs ) noexcept;
}}
{{dcl|num=2|since=c++23|1=
friend constexpr std::strong_ordering
    operator&lt;=&gt;( const stacktrace_entry&amp; lhs, const stacktrace_entry&amp; rhs ) noexcept;
}}
{{dcl end}}

@1@ Compares {{c|lhs}} and {{c|rhs}} for equality. Two {{tt|stacktrace_entry}} values are equal if and only if they represent the same stacktrace entry, or both of them are empty.

@2@ Gets the relative order between {{c|lhs}} and {{c|rhs}} in the unspecified strict total order over all {{tt|stacktrace_entry}} values which is consistent with the equality relation established by {{tt|1=operator==}}.

{{cpp/hidden friend|std::stacktrace_entry|plural=yes}}

{{cpp/note synthesized compare}}

===Parameters===
{{par begin}}
{{par|lhs, rhs|{{tt|stacktrace_entry}} values to compare}}
{{par end}}

===Return value===
@1@ {{c|true}} if two {{c|lhs}} and {{c|rhs}} compare equal, {{c|false}} otherwise.

@2@ {{lc|std::strong_ordering::equal}} if {{c|lhs}} and {{c|rhs}} compare equal.
@@ Otherwise, {{lc|std::strong_ordering::less}} if {{c|lhs}} is ordered before {{c|rhs}} in the strict total order.
@@ Otherwise, {{lc|std::strong_ordering::greater}} (in which case {{c|rhs}} is ordered before {{c|lhs}} in the strict total order).
